               <history>
                  <origin><origDate calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1863">1280 AH (1863
                        CE)</origDate></origin>
                  <provenance><p>Subsequently acquired by <persName type="supplied"
                           key="person_f830" role="fmo" change="#role-assignment">Colonel George
                           William Hamilton (1807-1868)</persName> who served in <placeName
                              cert="medium" ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7000208"
                              >India</placeName>
                        <date from="1823" to="1867"> from 1823 to 1867</date>, latterly as
                        Commissioner in <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7001535"
                           >Delhi</placeName>.</p></provenance>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>Hamilton acquired over a thousand Indian and Persian manuscripts which he
                        brought to Britain after he retired. After his death, the <orgName
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/134857252">British Museum</orgName> purchased
                        352 from his widow, <persName key="person_f8470" role="fmo">Charlotte Logie
                           Hamilton (1817–1893)</persName>, now held in the <orgName
                              ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/121814978">British Library</orgName>.</p>
                  </provenance>
                  <provenance><p>
                        <persName type="standard" role="fmo" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/97751058/"
                           key="person_97751058"> Alexander Lindsay, 25th Earl of Crawford
                           (1812–1880)</persName>, purchased the remainder in <date
                              calendar="#Gregorian" when="1868">1868</date> for <orgName
                                 ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/295427552" key="person_295427552">Bibliotheca
                                 Lindesiana</orgName> at Haigh Hall, <placeName
                                    ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7010384" key="place_7010384"
                                    >Wigan</placeName>.</p></provenance>
                  <provenance><p>Purchased by <persName key="person_f6379" role="dnr"
                           change="#prov-markup">Enriqueta Rylands (1843–1908)</persName> in <date
                              calendar="#Gregorian" when="1901">1901</date> from <persName
                                 type="standard" role="fmo" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/9985420/"
                                 key="person_9985420">James Ludovic Lindsay, 26th Earl of Crawford
                                 (1847–1913)</persName>.</p></provenance>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>Bequeathed by <persName type="standard" role="dnr" key="person_f6379"
                           >Enriqueta Rylands (1843–1908)</persName> in <date calendar="#Gregorian"
                              when="1908">1908</date> to the <orgName role="rps"
                                 ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/312795145/#John_Rylands_Library">John Rylands
                                 Library</orgName>.</p>
                  </acquisition>
               </history>
